HEADWORD: Lindia
<hw>Lin"di*a</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧n"d⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A peculiar genus of rotifers,
remarkable for the absence of ciliated disks. By some Zoologists it is
thought to be like the ancestral form of the Arthropoda.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lindiform</ent>⟦br⟧
